=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Compander_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright mixed sound, with complex oscillator character around 81 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: moderate
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 80.7574
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.2328
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5632
  pitch_clarity: 20.0713
  inharmonicity: 0.0086
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -15.5525
  resonance_freq: 129.1992

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Compander Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Compander.html
// Tags: Compander, Classes, dynamics
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
{
    Decay2.ar(
        Impulse.ar(8, 0, LFSaw.kr(0.3, 1, -0.3, 0.3)),
        0.001,
        0.3
    )
    * Mix.ar(Pulse.ar([80, 81], 0.3))
}.play;
)
